✨DIY UP-CYCLE TABLE ✨

Used chalk paint from @bluebirdpaints to paint this old table I had at my place to give it new life.
Chalk paints are especially made for use on furniture and are super easy to use. You dont have to sand or prime your
furniture just start painting, 2-3 coats and you are done with neat and professional look.(I added very little amount of water to dilute the paint, its not really needed but if you feel like its too thick you can.)
Products Used:
1. @bluebirdpaints Chalk Paint (sand dune)
2. Golden acrylic paint
* Overcoat with Polyurethane Clear Coat Matt after 24 hours of application as a sealant/wax. This is a necessary step
which ensures long lasting finish
and durability.

Ask any questions you have related to chalk paint in the comments and I'll help you out. 💕

✨ DIY MARBLE TRAY ✨

If you find these marble trays are quite expensive and want one too for your dresser this hack is for you. All you need is marble paper you can easily get from anywhere I got it from Daraz. You can get handles from any hardware store for a
very low price (50-100Rs) and any wood piece or anything similar can work. You can use different shapes to experiment. Wrap the marble paper around the wood and screw in the handles and you are done.
You can place it on your dresser, washroom, coffee table, or any place you like.

Pro Tip: If you want neater edges you can blow-dry the corners. My blower was not working but you should definitely
do it.

✨DIY VASE ✨

I found these vases at a random shop on the road and I knew I can turn these into something good. Really love these textured vases DIY trend so I gave it a try. 😍

1. Take white acrylic paint for the base coat. My paint was already very thick so I didn't add baking powder for the texture but if your paint is thin you can add baking powder to create texture.
2. Let the vases dry for 20-30 minutes and in the same white paint mixture add your desired paint color and do the
second coat.
3. For the white vase mix acrylic paint with water and sprinkle it on the vase with a paintbrush. 

And it is done. 

Let me know if you like the white vase more or the pink ones?

✨ scented candle at home ✨

Tried out making these scented candle at home and I am in love because its super affordable and really easy to make. 😍

• you can get all the stuff to make candle from daraz at a very affordable rate. 
• make sure you cool down your wax a bit before adding fragrance. 
• fill the candle container 3/4, once it cool down a bit add the rest of wax so its levelled. 
• you can add 8-9 drops of fragrance oil. 

Let me know if you have any other questions or any tips for me. ✨

✨ how to spice up a simple wall ✨

I wanted something completely different without changing my furniture or spending too much so this was it. On a cardboard I drew the shape I wanted. Stencilled it on the wall with pencil and painted it. And this console looked perfect with it. Added some stuff and tada. It has to be my favourite corner of my room. 😍

If you want to change the look of your room this is a great way. You can definitely experiment with the colours. If you have any questions I would be happy to help you in comments. ✨

*paint shade Hot pink (47) enamel master paint and the lighter one is mixed with white.
